Mark Hughes is confident his Stoke side will not be caught cold on Monday night when they play Rochdale at Spotland just days after returning from warm weather training in Dubai.

The Potters boss took his squad to balmy climes for a change of scenery as temperatures plunged last week.

Returning to the cold to face the Sky Bet League One side in the FA Cup fourth round may come as a shock to their system, but Hughes is unconcerned.

