'We are used to the weather in these parts and it won't take us long to get back into it,' he said.

'Hopefully, the surface will be OK. We know we've got to go there, face the conditions and get on with it. It won't faze us. We will take the challenge on and make sure we get the job done.'

Hughes explained: 'The training ground here is a little bit wet under foot at the moment and that obviously wasn't the case away, so we got some good work done,' he said.

'We've had two days leading into the game on Monday, so the structure of the week works for us.

'The break has done us good. We've just come through Christmas, which takes its toll on everybody.

